00058 /* NOTE: These must match what is checked in common-config.mk */
00059 /* Defines to represent the different versions of Octeon.  */
00060 
00061 /* IMPORTANT: When the default pass is updated for an Octeon Model,
00062 ** the corresponding change must also be made in the oct-sim script. */
00063 
00064 /* The defines below should be used with the OCTEON_IS_MODEL() macro to
00065 ** determine what model of chip the software is running on.  Models ending
00066 ** in 'XX' match multiple models (families), while specific models match only
00067 ** that model.  If a pass (revision) is specified, then only that revision
00068 ** will be matched.  Care should be taken when checking for both specific
00069 ** models and families that the specific models are checked for first.
00070 ** While these defines are similar to the processor ID, they are not intended
00071 ** to be used by anything other that the OCTEON_IS_MODEL framework, and
00072 ** the values are subject to change at anytime without notice.
00073 **
00074 ** NOTE: only the OCTEON_IS_MODEL() macro/function and the OCTEON_CN* macros
00075 ** should be used outside of this file.  All other macros are for internal
00076 ** use only, and may change without notice.
00077 */
00078

00082 /* Flag bits in top byte */
00083 #define OM_IGNORE_REVISION        0x01000000    /* Ignores revision in model checks */
00084 #define OM_CHECK_SUBMODEL         0x02000000    /* Check submodels */
00085 #define OM_MATCH_PREVIOUS_MODELS  0x04000000    /* Match all models previous than the one specified */
00086 #define OM_IGNORE_MINOR_REVISION  0x08000000    /* Ignores the minor revison on newer parts */
00087 #define OM_FLAG_MASK              0xff000000

00089 #define OM_MATCH_5XXX_FAMILY_MODELS     0x20000000  /* Match all cn5XXX Octeon models. */

00091 #define OM_MATCH_F7XXX_FAMILY_MODELS    0x80000000  /* Match all cnf7XXX Octeon models. */
00092 #define OM_MATCH_7XXX_FAMILY_MODELS     0x10000000  /* Match all cn7XXX Octeon models. */
00093 #define OM_MATCH_FAMILY_MODELS      (OM_MATCH_5XXX_FAMILY_MODELS | \
00094                      OM_MATCH_6XXX_FAMILY_MODELS | \
00095                      OM_MATCH_F7XXX_FAMILY_MODELS | \

00294 /* This matches the complete family of CN3xxx CPUs, and not subsequent models */
00295 #define OCTEON_CN3XXX           (OCTEON_CN58XX_PASS1_0 | OM_MATCH_PREVIOUS_MODELS | OM_IGNORE_REVISION)
00296 #define OCTEON_CN5XXX           (OCTEON_CN58XX_PASS1_0 | OM_MATCH_5XXX_FAMILY_MODELS)
00297 #define OCTEON_CN6XXX           (OCTEON_CN63XX_PASS1_0 | OM_MATCH_6XXX_FAMILY_MODELS)
00298 #define OCTEON_CNF7XXX          (OCTEON_CNF71XX_PASS1_0 | OM_MATCH_F7XXX_FAMILY_MODELS)
00299 #define OCTEON_CN7XXX           (OCTEON_CN78XX_PASS1_0 | OM_MATCH_7XXX_FAMILY_MODELS)
00300 
00301 /* The revision byte (low byte) has two different encodings.
00302 ** CN3XXX:
00303 **
00304 **     bits
00305 **     <7:5>: reserved (0)
00306 **     <4>:   alternate package
00307 **     <3:0>: revision
00308 **
00309 ** CN5XXX and older models:
00310 **
00311 **     bits
00312 **     <7>:   reserved (0)
00313 **     <6>:   alternate package
00314 **     <5:3>: major revision
00315 **     <2:0>: minor revision
00316 **
00317 */
00318 
00319 /* Masks used for the various types of model/family/revision matching */
00320 #define OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_MASK      0x00ffff00
00321 #define OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_REV_MASK  0x00ffff0f
00322 #define OCTEON_38XX_MODEL_MASK       0x00ffff10
00323 #define OCTEON_38XX_MODEL_REV_MASK   (OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_REV_MASK | OCTEON_38XX_MODEL_MASK)
00324 
00325 /* CN5XXX and later use different layout of bits in the revision ID field */
00326 #define OCTEON_58XX_FAMILY_MASK      OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_MASK
00327 #define OCTEON_58XX_FAMILY_REV_MASK  0x00ffff3f
00328 #define OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_MASK       0x00ffff40
00329 #define OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_REV_MASK   (OCTEON_58XX_FAMILY_REV_MASK | OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_MASK)
00330 #define OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_MINOR_REV_MASK (OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_REV_MASK & 0x00ffff38)
00331 #define OCTEON_5XXX_MODEL_MASK       0x00ff0fc0
00332 
00333 #define __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__(x,y,z) (((x) & (z)) == ((y) & (z)))
00334 
00335 /*
00336  * __OCTEON_IS_MODEL_COMPILE__(arg_model, chip_model)
00337  * returns true if chip_model is identical or belong to the OCTEON
00338  * model group specified in arg_model.
00339  *
00340  * NOTE: This for internal use only!!!!!
00341  */
00342 #define __OCTEON_IS_MODEL_COMPILE__(arg_model, chip_model) \
00343     ((((arg_model & OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_MASK) < OCTEON_CN58XX_PASS1_0)  && (\
00344      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == (OM_IGNORE_REVISION | OM_CHECK_SUBMODEL)) \
00345        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_38XX_MODEL_MASK)) || \
00346      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == 0) \
00347        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_REV_MASK)) || \
00348      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == OM_IGNORE_REVISION) \
00349        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_MASK)) || \
00350      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == OM_CHECK_SUBMODEL) \
00351        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_38XX_MODEL_REV_MASK)) || \
00352      ((((arg_model) & (OM_MATCH_PREVIOUS_MODELS)) == OM_MATCH_PREVIOUS_MODELS) \
00353        && (((chip_model) & OCTEON_38XX_MODEL_MASK) < ((arg_model) & OCTEON_38XX_MODEL_MASK))) \
00354     )) || \
00355     (((arg_model & OCTEON_38XX_FAMILY_MASK) >= OCTEON_CN58XX_PASS1_0)  && (\
00356      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == (OM_IGNORE_REVISION | OM_CHECK_SUBMODEL)) \
00357        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_MASK)) || \
00358      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == 0) \
00359        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_58XX_FAMILY_REV_MASK)) || \
00360      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == OM_IGNORE_MINOR_REVISION) \
00361        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_MINOR_REV_MASK)) || \
00362      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == OM_CHECK_SUBMODEL) \
00363        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_58XX_MODEL_MASK)) || \
00364      ((((arg_model) & (OM_FLAG_MASK)) == OM_IGNORE_REVISION) \
00365        && __OCTEON_MATCH_MASK__((chip_model), (arg_model), OCTEON_58XX_FAMILY_MASK)) || \
00366      ((((arg_model) & (OM_MATCH_5XXX_FAMILY_MODELS)) == OM_MATCH_5XXX_FAMILY_MODELS) \
00367        && ((chip_model & OCTEON_PRID_MASK) >= OCTEON_CN58XX_PASS1_0) && ((chip_model & OCTEON_PRID_MASK) < OCTEON_CN63XX_PASS1_0)) || \
00368      ((((arg_model) & (OM_MATCH_6XXX_FAMILY_MODELS)) == OM_MATCH_6XXX_FAMILY_MODELS) \
00369        && ((chip_model & OCTEON_PRID_MASK) >= OCTEON_CN63XX_PASS1_0) && ((chip_model & OCTEON_PRID_MASK) < OCTEON_CNF71XX_PASS1_0)) || \
00370      ((((arg_model) & (OM_MATCH_F7XXX_FAMILY_MODELS)) == OM_MATCH_F7XXX_FAMILY_MODELS) \

00398 /* The OCTEON_IS_MODEL macro should be used for all Octeon model checking done
00399 ** in a program.
00400 ** This should be kept runtime if at all possible  and must be conditionalized
00401 ** with OCTEON_IS_COMMON_BINARY() if runtime checking support is required.
00402 **
00403 ** Use of the macro in preprocessor directives ( #if OCTEON_IS_MODEL(...) )
00404 ** is NOT SUPPORTED, and should be replaced with CVMX_COMPILED_FOR()
00405 ** I.e.:
00406 **  #if OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN56XX)  ->  #if CVMX_COMPILED_FOR(OCTEON_CN56XX)
00407 */
00408 #define OCTEON_IS_MODEL(x) __octeon_is_model_runtime__(x)
00409 #define OCTEON_IS_COMMON_BINARY() 1
00410 #undef OCTEON_MODEL
00411 #else
00412 #define CVMX_COMPILED_FOR(x) __OCTEON_IS_MODEL_COMPILE__(x, OCTEON_MODEL)
00413 
00414 #define OCTEON_IS_MODEL(x) \
00415     (((x & (OM_IGNORE_REVISION | OM_IGNORE_MINOR_REVISION | OM_MATCH_FAMILY_MODELS)) != 0) \
00416     ? __OCTEON_IS_MODEL_COMPILE__(x, OCTEON_MODEL) \
00417     : __OCTEON_IS_MODEL_COMPILE__(x, cvmx_get_proc_id()))
00418 
00419 #define OCTEON_IS_COMMON_BINARY() 0
00420 #endif
00421 #endif

00435 /**
00436  * Return the octeon family, i.e., ProcessorID of the PrID register.
00437  *
00438  * @return the octeon family on success, ((unint32_t)-1) on error.
00439  */
00440 static inline uint32_t cvmx_get_octeon_family(void)
00441 {
00442 #if defined(USE_RUNTIME_MODEL_CHECKS) || defined(__U_BOOT__) || (defined(__linux__) && defined(__KERNEL__)) || defined(CVMX_BUILD_FOR_TOOLCHAIN)
00443     return (cvmx_get_proc_id() & OCTEON_FAMILY_MASK);
00444 #else

00446 #endif
